26/**
27* Enumerates barcode formats known to this package.
28*/
29enum class BarcodeFormat
30{
31 // The values are an implementation detail. The c++ use-case (ZXing::Flags) could have been designed such that it
32 // would not have been necessary to explicitly set the values to single bit constants. This has been done to ease
33 // the interoperability with C-like interfaces, the python and the Qt wrapper.
34 INVALID = 0, ///< Used as a return value if no valid barcode has been detected
35 AZTEC = (1 << 0), ///< Aztec (2D)
36 CODABAR = (1 << 1), ///< CODABAR (1D)
37 CODE_39 = (1 << 2), ///< Code 39 (1D)
38 CODE_93 = (1 << 3), ///< Code 93 (1D)
39 CODE_128 = (1 << 4), ///< Code 128 (1D)
40 DATA_MATRIX = (1 << 5), ///< Data Matrix (2D)
41 EAN_8 = (1 << 6), ///< EAN-8 (1D)
42 EAN_13 = (1 << 7), ///< EAN-13 (1D)
43 ITF = (1 << 8), ///< ITF (Interleaved Two of Five) (1D)
44 MAXICODE = (1 << 9), ///< MaxiCode (2D)
45 PDF_417 = (1 << 10), ///< PDF417 (1D) or (2D)
46 QR_CODE = (1 << 11), ///< QR Code (2D)
47 RSS_14 = (1 << 12), ///< RSS 14
48 RSS_EXPANDED = (1 << 13), ///< RSS EXPANDED
49 UPC_A = (1 << 14), ///< UPC-A (1D)
50 UPC_E = (1 << 15), ///< UPC-E (1D)
51 UPC_EAN_EXTENSION = (1 << 16), ///< UPC/EAN extension (1D). Not a stand-alone format.
52
53 FORMAT_COUNT = INVALID, ///> DEPRECATED: Used to count the number of formats
54 _max = UPC_EAN_EXTENSION, ///> implementation detail, don't use
55};
